<subSubSection id="8CFE651F2B48FF8D3AD52E9DCBA38064" pageId="51" pageNumber="52" type="diagnosis">
<paragraph id="C45B36942B48FF8D3AD52E9DCBA38064" blockId="51.[151,1437,829,2044]" pageId="51" pageNumber="52">
<emphasis id="F690EA862B48FF8D3AD52E9DCE2686EF" bold="true" box="[199,322,901,928]" pageId="51" pageNumber="52">Diagnosis.</emphasis>
The small species is defined externally by the white forewing with three dark brown fasciae and black spot in middle and in the corner of cell. 
<taxonomicName id="03E44D172B48FF8D38BE2EB2CCAE868C" authority="Povolny, 1972" authorityName="Povolny" authorityYear="1972" box="[684,970,937,964]" class="Insecta" family="Gelechiidae" genus="Scrobipalpa" kingdom="Animalia" order="Lepidoptera" pageId="51" pageNumber="52" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="brandti">
<emphasis id="F690EA862B48FF8D38BE2EB2CC78868C" box="[684,796,937,964]" italics="true" pageId="51" pageNumber="52">S. brandti</emphasis>
<bibRefCitation id="A0754B652B48FF8D39372EB1CCAE868C" author="Povolny, D." box="[805,970,937,963]" pageId="51" pageNumber="52" pagination="186 - 206" refId="ref58386" refString="Povolny, D. (1972) Zur Fauna der Tribus Gnorimoschemini (Lepidoptera, Gelechiidae) im Iran. Acta entomologica bohemoslovaca, 69, 186 - 206." type="journal article" year="1972">Povolný, 1972</bibRefCitation>
</taxonomicName>
and 
<taxonomicName id="03E44D172B48FF8D3E162EB2CA7E868C" authority="Piskunov, 1900" authorityName="Piskunov" authorityYear="1900" box="[1028,1306,937,964]" class="Insecta" family="Gelechiidae" genus="Scrobipalpa" kingdom="Animalia" order="Lepidoptera" pageId="51" pageNumber="52" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="sinevi">
<emphasis id="F690EA862B48FF8D3E162EB2CB06868C" box="[1028,1122,938,964]" italics="true" pageId="51" pageNumber="52">S. sinevi</emphasis>
Piskunov, 1900
</taxonomicName>
are lighter, without black markings, the fasciae are light brown rather than dark brown. The transverse posterior margin of vinculum in combination with sub-triangular sacculus and narrow saccus are characteristic for the male genitalia. 
<taxonomicName id="03E44D172B48FF8D3A85290ECE9C817F" authority="(Sircom, 1850)" authorityName="Sircom" authorityYear="1850" baseAuthorityName="Sircom" baseAuthorityYear="1850" box="[151,504,1045,1072]" class="Insecta" family="Gelechiidae" genus="Scrobipalpa" kingdom="Animalia" order="Lepidoptera" pageId="51" pageNumber="52" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="acuminatella">
<emphasis id="F690EA862B48FF8D3A85290ECE228160" box="[151,326,1045,1072]" italics="true" pageId="51" pageNumber="52">S. acuminatella</emphasis>
(Sircom, 1850)
</taxonomicName>
is similar in having the transverse posterior margin of vinculum but differs in subrectangular rather than sub-triangular sacculus, the broader saccus and tapered rather than sub-rectangular vincular process (see for comparison 
<bibRefCitation id="A0754B652B48FF8D3BF12946CC2D8137" author="Huemer, P. &amp; Karsholt, O." box="[483,841,1117,1144]" pageId="51" pageNumber="52" refId="ref56993" refString="Huemer, P. &amp; Karsholt, O. (2010) Gelechiidae II (Gelechiinae: Gnorimoschemini). In: Huemer, P., Karsholt, O. &amp; Nuss, M. (Eds.), Microlepidoptera of Europe. Vol. 6. Apollo Books, Stenstrup, 586 pp. https: // doi. org / 10.1163 / 9789004260986" type="book" year="2010">Huemer &amp; Karsholt 2010: 375</bibRefCitation>
, fig. 17). 
<taxonomicName id="03E44D172B48FF8D39AF2946CB958138" authority="Povolny, 1967" authorityName="Povolny" authorityYear="1967" box="[957,1265,1117,1144]" class="Insecta" family="Gelechiidae" genus="Scrobipalpa" kingdom="Animalia" order="Lepidoptera" pageId="51" pageNumber="52" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="heratella">
<emphasis id="F690EA862B48FF8D39AF2946CB258138" box="[957,1089,1117,1144]" italics="true" pageId="51" pageNumber="52">S. heratella</emphasis>
Povolný, 1967
</taxonomicName>
has somewhat similar posterior margin of vinculum and vincular process but differs in the longer uncus, larger sacculus and weakly inflated caecum of the phallus (
<bibRefCitation id="A0754B652B48FF8D385C29BDCD8B81F0" author="Povolny, D." box="[590,751,1189,1215]" pageId="51" pageNumber="52" refId="ref58484" refString="Povolny, D. (2002) Iconograhia tribus Gnorimoschemini (Lepidoptera, Gelechiidae) Regionis Palaearcticae. Frantisek Slamka Publ., Bratislava, 110 pp., 16 colour pls., 87 pls." type="book" year="2002">Povolný 2002</bibRefCitation>
: Pl. 8, fig. 73). The female genitalia can be recognized by the strongly edged anteromedial emargination of sternum VIII and narrow medially curved signum. Some other species of 
<taxonomicName id="03E44D172B48FF8D3AA429F5CE5A8048" authorityName="Janse" authorityYear="1951" box="[182,318,1261,1287]" class="Insecta" family="Gelechiidae" genus="Scrobipalpa" kingdom="Animalia" order="Lepidoptera" pageId="51" pageNumber="52" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="genus">
<emphasis id="F690EA862B48FF8D3AA429F5CE5A8048" box="[182,318,1261,1287]" italics="true" pageId="51" pageNumber="52">Scrobipalpa</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
(e.g. 
<taxonomicName id="03E44D172B48FF8D3B9229F6CDD38048" authority="Povolny, 1971" authorityName="Povolny" authorityYear="1971" box="[384,695,1261,1288]" class="Insecta" family="Gelechiidae" genus="Scrobipalpa" kingdom="Animalia" order="Lepidoptera" pageId="51" pageNumber="52" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="albofusca">
<emphasis id="F690EA862B48FF8D3B9229F6CD6D8048" box="[384,521,1261,1288]" italics="true" pageId="51" pageNumber="52">S. albofusca</emphasis>
Povolný, 1971
</taxonomicName>
, 
<taxonomicName id="03E44D172B48FF8D38D629F6CC898048" authority="Povolny, 1981" authorityName="Povolny" authorityYear="1981" box="[708,1005,1261,1288]" class="Insecta" family="Gelechiidae" genus="Scrobipalpa" kingdom="Animalia" order="Lepidoptera" pageId="51" pageNumber="52" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="sindibad">
<emphasis id="F690EA862B48FF8D38D629F6CC258048" box="[708,833,1261,1288]" italics="true" pageId="51" pageNumber="52">S. sindibad</emphasis>
Povolný, 1981
</taxonomicName>
and 
<taxonomicName id="03E44D172B48FF8D3E3729F6CA338048" authority="Povolny, 1977" authorityName="Povolny" authorityYear="1977" box="[1061,1367,1261,1288]" class="Insecta" family="Gelechiidae" genus="Scrobipalpa" kingdom="Animalia" order="Lepidoptera" pageId="51" pageNumber="52" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="superstes">
<emphasis id="F690EA862B48FF8D3E3729F6CBCE8048" box="[1061,1194,1262,1288]" italics="true" pageId="51" pageNumber="52">S. superstes</emphasis>
Povolný, 1977
</taxonomicName>
) have somewhat similar female genitalia but differ in the above mentioned and some other characters.
</paragraph>
</subSubSection>
<subSubSection id="8CFE651F2B48FF8D3AD5282DCD1082B4" pageId="51" pageNumber="52" type="description">
<paragraph id="C45B36942B48FF8D3AD5282DCC92834B" blockId="51.[151,1437,829,2044]" pageId="51" pageNumber="52">
<emphasis id="F690EA862B48FF8D3AD5282DCEC5801F" bold="true" box="[199,417,1333,1360]" pageId="51" pageNumber="52">Description. Adult</emphasis>
(
<figureCitation id="5CDF2A112B48FF8D3BA2282DCD60801F" box="[432,516,1333,1360]" captionStart="FIGS 36–38" captionStartId="24.[151,210,1711,1736]" captionTargetBox="[157,1421,186,1674]" captionTargetId="figure@24.[154,1433,181,1686]" captionText="FIGS 36–38. Scrobipalpa aravensis sp. n. 36. Adult, Holotype, ♀ (gen. slide 136/18, O. Bidzilya). 37. Male genitalia, paratype (gen. slide 127/18, O. Bidzilya). 37a. Posterior margin of vinculum and sacculi (enlarged). 38. Female genitalia, holotype (gen. slide 136/18, O. Bidzilya)." figureDoi="http://doi.org/10.5281/zenodo.3468888" httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/3468888/files/figure.png" pageId="51" pageNumber="52">Fig. 36</figureCitation>
). Wingspan. 7.0 mm (
<specimenCount id="D2E2FD1D2B48FF8D38E5282DCC618000" box="[759,773,1333,1359]" pageId="51" pageNumber="52" type="female">♀</specimenCount>
)—7.7 (
<specimenCount id="D2E2FD1D2B48FF8D3976282DCC1E8000" box="[868,890,1333,1359]" pageId="51" pageNumber="52" type="male">♂</specimenCount>
) mm. Head, thorax and tegulae white with single yellow or light brown-tipped scales. Labial palpus white with light brown basal and apical rings, inner surface of segment 2 entirely white, scape brown, antennal segment brown and white ringed; forewing white, dorsal margin weakly mottled with light brown, three transverse dark brown fasciae at base, before middle and at 2/3 length, diffuse black spot with few ochreous scales in mid-width within the second fascia, several black scales in the corner of cell, apex mixed with brown, cilia white, brown-tipped. Hindwing light grey.
</paragraph>
<paragraph id="C45B36942B48FF8D3AD52B16CDDA83B0" blockId="51.[151,1437,829,2044]" pageId="51" pageNumber="52">
<emphasis id="F690EA862B48FF8D3AD52B16CE178367" bold="true" box="[199,371,1549,1576]" pageId="51" pageNumber="52">Male genitalia</emphasis>
(
<figureCitation id="5CDF2A112B48FF8D3B912B15CEBC8368" box="[387,472,1549,1575]" captionStart="FIGS 36–38" captionStartId="24.[151,210,1711,1736]" captionTargetBox="[157,1421,186,1674]" captionTargetId="figure@24.[154,1433,181,1686]" captionText="FIGS 36–38. Scrobipalpa aravensis sp. n. 36. Adult, Holotype, ♀ (gen. slide 136/18, O. Bidzilya). 37. Male genitalia, paratype (gen. slide 127/18, O. Bidzilya). 37a. Posterior margin of vinculum and sacculi (enlarged). 38. Female genitalia, holotype (gen. slide 136/18, O. Bidzilya)." figureDoi="http://doi.org/10.5281/zenodo.3468888" httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/3468888/files/figure.png" pageId="51" pageNumber="52">Fig. 37</figureCitation>
). Uncus longer than broad, weakly narrowed, posterior margin weakly rounded; gnathos short; tegumen sub-triangular, anteromedial emargination deep, broadly rounded; valva gradually curved, apex weakly broadened, extending to the top of uncus; sacculus about 1/3 length of valva, broad at base, gradually curved inwards, distal portion narrowly tapered towards pointed tip, gap to valva big; posterior margin of vinculum transverse laterally, with deep and broad v-shaped medial emargination, vincular process short, sub-rectangular, extending below tip of sacculus; saccus slender, extending far beyond apex of pedunculus; phallus short, straight, caecum strongly inflated, rounded, half length of phallus.
</paragraph>
<paragraph id="C45B36942B48FF8D3AD52A12CD1082B4" blockId="51.[151,1437,829,2044]" pageId="51" pageNumber="52">
<emphasis id="F690EA862B48FF8D3AD52A12CEEF826B" bold="true" box="[199,395,1801,1828]" pageId="51" pageNumber="52">Female genitalia</emphasis>
(
<figureCitation id="5CDF2A112B48FF8D3B8B2A11CE88826C" box="[409,492,1801,1827]" captionStart="FIGS 36–38" captionStartId="24.[151,210,1711,1736]" captionTargetBox="[157,1421,186,1674]" captionTargetId="figure@24.[154,1433,181,1686]" captionText="FIGS 36–38. Scrobipalpa aravensis sp. n. 36. Adult, Holotype, ♀ (gen. slide 136/18, O. Bidzilya). 37. Male genitalia, paratype (gen. slide 127/18, O. Bidzilya). 37a. Posterior margin of vinculum and sacculi (enlarged). 38. Female genitalia, holotype (gen. slide 136/18, O. Bidzilya)." figureDoi="http://doi.org/10.5281/zenodo.3468888" httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/3468888/files/figure.png" pageId="51" pageNumber="52">Fig. 38</figureCitation>
). Papillae anales sub-ovate, covered with short setae; apophyses posteriores 3.5 times as long as apophyses anteriores; segment VIII as broad as long, subgenital plates broadly separated, covered with microtrichia, with honey-comb sclerotized patches extending posteriorly from the base of apophyses anteriores to 2/3 length of medial margin, ventromedial depression weakly sclerotized, not extending beyond the anterior margin of sternum VIII, anteromedial emargination of segment VIII deep, triangular, strongly edged; apophyses anteriores as long as segment VIII; colliculum narrow, ductus bursae gradually broadened towards elongated corpus bursae; signum narrow, strongly curved in middle.
</paragraph>
</subSubSection>
<subSubSection id="8CFE651F2B4FFF8A3AD52D80CBA985B4" pageId="52" pageNumber="53" type="biology_ecology">
<paragraph id="C45B36942B4FFF8A3AD52D80CBA985B4" blockId="52.[151,1437,152,323]" pageId="52" pageNumber="53">
<emphasis id="F690EA862B4FFF8A3AD52D80CE4385FC" bold="true" box="[199,295,152,179]" pageId="52" pageNumber="53">Biology.</emphasis>
Host plant unknown. Adults have been collected in late March. Both of the localities are situated in the Arava Valley which is harsh desert in the southern part of 
<collectingCountry id="BCF376042B4FFF8A395F2DA5CCEF8598" box="[845,907,189,215]" name="Israel" pageId="52" pageNumber="53">Israel</collectingCountry>
characterized by riverbed vegetation only. The annual precipitation is low, with number of rain days per year ranging from 0 to 10 (
<bibRefCitation id="A0754B652B4FFF8A3E542DF9CBA585B4" author="Jaffe, S." box="[1094,1217,225,251]" pageId="52" pageNumber="53" pagination="79 - 95" refId="ref57178" refString="Jaffe, S. (1988) Climate of Israel. In: Yom-Tov, Y. &amp; Tchernov, J. (Eds.), The Zoogeography of Israel. The Distribution and Abundance at a Zoogeographical Crossroad. Dr W. Junk Publishers, Dordrecht, Boston &amp; Lancaster, pp. 79 - 95." type="book chapter" year="1988">Jaffe 1988</bibRefCitation>
).
</paragraph>
</subSubSection>
<subSubSection id="8CFE651F2B4FFF8A3AD52C1CCDD78450" box="[199,691,260,287]" pageId="52" pageNumber="53" type="distribution">
<paragraph id="C45B36942B4FFF8A3AD52C1CCDD78450" blockId="52.[151,1437,152,323]" box="[199,691,260,287]" pageId="52" pageNumber="53">
<emphasis id="F690EA862B4FFF8A3AD52C1CCE058450" bold="true" box="[199,353,260,287]" pageId="52" pageNumber="53">Distribution.</emphasis>
<collectingCountry id="BCF376042B4FFF8A3B752C1DCECE8450" box="[359,426,261,287]" name="Israel" pageId="52" pageNumber="53">Israel</collectingCountry>
: Shezaf Nature reserve.
</paragraph>
</subSubSection>
<subSubSection id="8CFE651F2B4FFF8A3AD52C31CBC8840C" box="[199,1196,297,323]" pageId="52" pageNumber="53" type="etymology">
<paragraph id="C45B36942B4FFF8A3AD52C31CBC8840C" blockId="52.[151,1437,152,323]" box="[199,1196,297,323]" pageId="52" pageNumber="53">
<emphasis id="F690EA862B4FFF8A3AD52C31CE2A840C" bold="true" box="[199,334,297,323]" pageId="52" pageNumber="53">Etymology.</emphasis>
The species is named after its 
<typeStatus id="1B5F88362B4FFF8A38B42C31CDB2840C" box="[678,726,297,323]" pageId="52" pageNumber="53">type</typeStatus>
locality—Arava desert in southern 
<collectingCountry id="BCF376042B4FFF8A3E742C31CBCC840C" box="[1126,1192,297,323]" name="Israel" pageId="52" pageNumber="53">Israel</collectingCountry>
.
</paragraph>
</subSubSection>
